deck: The Kingpin manipulates the old web-head.
description: The Federal Bureau of Investigation (FBI) enlists the aid of your friendly neighborhood Spider-Man to obtain the TX-1 microchip, which is used for decryption of satellite transmissions to international markets. However, he realizes that this is all just a scam pulled by the Kingpin himself.
name: Royal Scam

deck: Dr. Curt Connors becomes the Lizard.
description: Something startling is happening to Dr. Connors, Peter's Chemistry professor. After testing a serum that he and Peter made, he goes on a reptilian metamorphosis and is on a rampage in Manhattan. But why is he targeting Harry Osborn?
name: Law of the Jungle

deck: A duel to the death with Spider-Man vs. the mysterious Shikata.
description:
Shikata, a powerful fighter who uses her magic sword in combat, is on the hunt for Spider-Man for money. She must capture Spidey for the guy who hired, who is looking to complete his collection of rare animals. However, she believes that Spidey is noble and she decides to kill him or be killed.

Note: Shikata is primarily based on Elektra
name: The Sword of Shikata

deck: Peter discovers that Harry Osborn's girlfriend is a thief named Talon!
description:
A master thief is on the loose in New York City. Daily Bugle calls her Talon, and she is committing several robberies all throughout the city. When Peter learns that she is Harry's new girlfriend, he must find a way to make her stop her criminal ways.

Note 1: Talon has no relation to this Talon or this Talon. Instead, she is an original character of the series.

Note 2: Talon is primarily based on Black Cat.
name: Keeping Secrets

deck: Three former KGB agents take a television station hostage, and Peter Parker is in the middle of it.
description:
Looking for a quick buck, Peter convinced J. Jonah Jameson to allow him to send a tape to the Empire-1 news studio. There, he met his new crush, Indira Daimonji, an intern working at the studio. But the sweet morning was broken when a group called Pterodax take the entire studio. These ex-KGB agents have one simple demand: Either Spider-Man drops by to fight, or they blow the entire newsroom sky high! There is one problem, Peter is one of the hostages. Menwhile, MJ feels that she and Peter have a gap between them and she plans to resolve it.

Note: The Pterodax group is primarily based on the characteristics of Vulture.
name: Tight Squeeze

deck: The new origin story of Iron Man!
description: Following the presumed death of Howard Stark, Tony is sent to school at orders of his father's friend, Obadiah Stane. Soon after, he discovers that a man who calls himself, "The Mandarin", has a connection with his father's death, including the mysterious Makluan Rings. Now, Tony must suit up and find out who he is.
name: Iron, Forged In Fire: Part One
